> 1. The coil is not the Bosch Blue -- it's a black one from the local FLAPS.
>
> 2. Plugs are Bosch (regular, not "super").
>
> 3. Rotor, cap and wires are from FLAPS.
>
> 4. Points are Bosch
>
> 5. When she runs, she runs great -- smooth idle and acceleration, no
> backfiring, no hesitation. When this happens, she basically just cuts out
> without warning -- no sputtering, etc.
>
>
> What am I missing here? I know that points are a regular "wear" item, but
